-- Threadneedle Says Goldman's Cielinski Will Head Fixed Income From October
-- Matthew Brown
-- 2010-07-15T13:20:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/threadneedle-appoints-goldman-sach-s-jim-cielinski-to-head-fixed-income.html

          
          
             Threadneedle Asset Management Ltd.
said it hired Jim Cielinski as head of fixed income from Goldman
Sachs Group Inc.  
 Cielinski will join Threadneedle in October to lead a team
that manages institutional and retail funds worth 22.6 billion
pounds ($34.8 billion) across government bonds, investment
grade, high yield, emerging market debt, Treasuries and asset-
backed securities, the company said in an e-mailed statement.  
 Cielinski spent 12 years at Goldman Sachs, most recently as
managing director and head of global investment-grade credit,
Threadneedle said.  
